Package: titled
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 Title Network is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Title Network uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Title
 Network client is the name of the open source software which enables the 
 use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the daemon, titled, and the CLI tool
 title-cli to interact with the daemon.

Package: title-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 Title Network is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Title Network uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Title
 Network client is the name of the open source software which enables the
 use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides Title-Qt, a GUI for Title Network based on Qt.

Package: title-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 Title Network is an experimental new digital currency that enables instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Title Network uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Title
 Network client is the name of the open source software which enables the
 use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides title-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a title network daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
